<item>
            <title>[LU-11478] LNet: discovery sequence numbers could be misleading</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11478</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a sequence number used when sending discovery messages. This sequence number is intended to detect stale messages. However it could be misleading if the peer reboots. In this case the peer&apos;s sequence number will reset. The node will think that all information being sent to it is stale, while in reality the peer might&apos;ve changed configuration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no reliable why to know whether a peer rebooted, so we&apos;ll always assume that the messages we&apos;re receiving are valid. So we&apos;ll operate on the first come first serve basis.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
